text: Nyctimystes latratus is a tree frog from Papua New Guinea. It lives between 500 and 1200 meters above sea level on Mount Dayman and near the Bai-u River. This frog has gold eyes. This frog is light brown or dark brown with a dull white belly. The name of this frog is from the Latin word latros for "to bark." ==References== Category:Frogs of Oceania
title: Nyctimystes latratus
